HEADWORD: phyllome
<hw>phyl"lome</hw> <pr>(f⟦icr⟧l"l⟦omac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>fy`llwma</grk> foliage, fr. <grk>fy`llon</grk> a leaf.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A foliar part of a plant; any organ homologous
with a leaf, or produced by metamorphosis of a leaf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phyllomorphosis</ent>⟦br⟧
